      "message": "if i never have to review another ad-hoc linked-list implementation again ...\n\ni\u0027m struggling to understand why you need this.  a config file is just a continuous \u0026 frozen vector of lines, like an argv, and once read, you\u0027re not changing it.  so treat it as such ?\n\nyou can use realloc to quickly extend the array of pointers, and a good allocator (like glibc should have) should make it fast by internally carving out space larger than you need.  or you could manage the line count yourself and over allocate too while initially reading.",
