      "side": 1,
      "message": "given a large enough config file, this will hang.  you cannot shovel unlimited data into a pipe -- the kernel will eventually block when it\u0027s full.\n\nsee \"pipe capacity\" in the pipe(7) man page:\nhttps://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man7/pipe.7.html\n\nsince the pipe wasn\u0027t created with O_NONBLOCK, the \"if write fails 3 times\" logic below won\u0027t kick in.  not that i\u0027m saying \"use nonblocking pipe\" to address this fundamental issue.\n\nthe limitation is prob fine in a small unittest, but not in a general utility module.",
